data.enText: a large round container without a lid, used for washing clothes in, growing plants in, etc.
There were tubs of flowers on the balcony.
a small wide, usually round, plastic or paper container with a lid, used for food, etc.

data.chText: 他们发现她躺在浴缸里。
data.enText: They found her lying in the tub.

word_means: 使入浴；为…洗澡；使…用练赛艇练习；把…种在木盆里

means: 使入浴；(在浴缸里)为…洗澡；使…用练赛艇练习；把…种在木盆里

tr: a relatively large open container that you fill with water and use to wash the body
a large open vessel for holding or storing liquids
the amount that a tub will hold

value.def: A tub is a deep container of any size.

example.ex: He peeled the paper top off a little white tub and poured the cream into his coffee...
example.tran: 他把小白盒上的纸盖撕去，然后把奶油倒进他的咖啡里。

example.ex: Shrubs can be grown in tubs or large containers.
example.tran: 灌木可以种植在盆里或大型容器中。

posc.def: A tub of something is the amount of it contained in a tub.

example.ex: She would eat four tubs of ice cream in one sitting.
example.tran: 她以前常常一次就吃4桶冰激凌。

value.def: A tub is the same as a bathtub .

example.ex: She lay back in the tub.
example.tran: 她向后靠着躺在浴缸里。

trans: 摸彩桶(内有藏在麸皮、纸等中的奖品，供儿童游戏用)
热水浴池(常置于室外，可供数人坐在里面休息)
